{"title_page": "Samrong BTS station", "text_new": "{{Infobox station\n| name = [[File:BTS E15.svg|40px]]<br/>Samrong\n| native_name = \u0e2a\u0e33\u0e42\u0e23\u0e07\n| native_name_lang = th\n| other_name = \n| type = {{rint|bangkok|Sukhumvit}}\n{{rint|bangkok|Yellow}}\n| image = BTS_Samrong_station.jpg\n| address = [[Mueang Samut Prakan District|Mueang Samut Prakan]], [[Samut Prakan Province|Samut Prakan]], [[Thailand]]\n| owned = [[Bangkok Metropolitan Administration]] (BMA)\n| operator            = [[BTS Group Holdings|Bangkok Mass Transit System<br>Public Company Limited]] (BTSC)\n| coordinates = {{coord|13.647363|100.596153}}\n| line = {{rail color box|system=BTS|line=Sukhumvit}}\n{{rail color box|system=Bangkok MRT|line=Yellow}} ''(Yellow Line opening 2021)''\n| other = \n| code = E15 (Sukhumvit line)<br/>''YL25 (Yellow line)''\n| opened = 3 April 2017\n| image_size = \n| image_caption = \n | services=\n{{s-rail|title=Bangkok Rapid Transit}}\n{{s-line|system=BTS|line=Sukhumvit|previous=Bearing|next=Pu Chao|type=North|type2=East}}\n}}\n\n[[File:BTS E15 Traditional station sign (MRTA Standard).svg|thumb|Samrong Station Traditional sign]]\n'''Samrong''' ({{lang-th|\u0e2a\u0e16\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e33\u0e42\u0e23\u0e07}}, {{RTGS|''Sathani Samrong''}}, {{IPA-th|s\u0101.t\u02b0\u01ce\u02d0.n\u012b\u02d0 s\u01cem.r\u014d\u02d0\u014b|pron}}) is a [[Bangkok Skytrain|BTS Skytrain]] station, on the [[Sukhumvit Line]] in [[Samut Prakan]], [[Thailand]].\n\nTrial operation began in March 2017, and the station was officially opened by Prime Minister [[Prayut Chan-o-cha]] on 3 April 2017,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nationmultimedia.com/news/national/30311133|title=Public to get free trial, as Samrong BTS station now opens \u2013 The Nation|work=The Nation|access-date=2017-04-03|language=en}}</ref> with passengers able to ride the extension for free for a month beginning on 4 April 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://coconuts.co/bangkok/news/bts-offers-free-rides-new-station-first-samut-prakarn/|title=BTS offers free rides to new station, first in Samut Prakarn {{!}} Coconuts Bangkok|date=2017-03-16|work=Coconuts|access-date=2017-04-01|language=en-US}}</ref> It was the eastern terminus of the line, until the opening of the other stations of the [[Sukhumvit Line]] Extension (East) on 6 December 2018. In future it will connect to the [[MRT Yellow Line]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pattayamail.com/thailandnews/bearing-samrong-segment-bts-green-line-put-trial-run-167271|title=Bearing-Samrong segment of BTS Green Line put on trial run - Pattaya It is one of the 2 stations which have an island platform, the other to be Siam station. Mail|last=Mail|first=Pattaya|date=2017-03-16|work=Pattaya Mail|access-date=2017-04-01|language=en-US}}</ref> It is one of only three BTS stations to have island platforms, with the other being [[Siam BTS station|Siam]], [[Ha Yaek Lat Phrao BTS station|Ha Yaek Lat Phrao]] and [[Wat Phra Si Mahathat BTS station|Wat Phra Si Mahathat station]].\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bangkok Skytrain]]\n{{Sukhumvit Line navbox}}\n\n[[Category:BTS Skytrain stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 2017]]\n\n\n{{Bangkok-geo-stub}}\n{{Thailand-rail-transport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n| name = [[File:BTS E15.svg|40px]]<br/>Samrong\n| native_name = \u0e2a\u0e33\u0e42\u0e23\u0e07\n| native_name_lang = th\n| other_name = \n| type = {{rint|bangkok|Sukhumvit}}\n{{rint|bangkok|Yellow}}\n| image = BTS_Samrong_station.jpg\n| address = [[Mueang Samut Prakan District|Mueang Samut Prakan]], [[Samut Prakan Province|Samut Prakan]], [[Thailand]]\n| owned = [[Bangkok Metropolitan Administration]] (BMA)\n| operator            = [[BTS Group Holdings|Bangkok Mass Transit System<br>Public Company Limited]] (BTSC)\n| coordinates = {{coord|13.647363|100.596153}}\n| line = {{rail color box|system=BTS|line=Sukhumvit}}\n{{rail color box|system=Bangkok MRT|line=Yellow}} ''(Yellow Line opening 2021)